A video of a shooting that took place in Berea, Durban over
the weekend has surfaced on social media. In the video, a group of men can be seen walking around on the road. It is alleged that an argument started in a taxi, and the taxi driver stopped and they got off. One of the men allegedly cocked his firearm which jammed. Then the alleged off-duty cop instructed the suspect to put down his gun, following that he took out his service gun and shot at a the suspect across the road. It's reported that a 9mm gun was allegedly recovered from
the suspect. One of the suspects was taken to hospital, where he allegedly
later died. 